Great! The fix has been successfully applied. Let me verify that the change is correct by reviewing the context:

The original code had:
```c
remove_ul_config_req_pdu(j, ul_config_req);
j--;
num_pdus--;
```

And now it has:
```c
remove_ul_config_req_pdu(j, ul_config_req);
j--;
num_pdus = ul_config_req->ul_config_request_body.number_of_pdus;
```

This is exactly what the PR description requested. The issue was that `remove_ul_config_req_pdu()` internally decrements `ul_config_req->ul_config_request_body.number_of_pdus` by shifting PDU entries, but the caller was also decrementing its local copy `num_pdus`. This divergence caused incorrect loop conditions.

The fix ensures that after calling `remove_ul_config_req_pdu()`, the local variable `num_pdus` is re-synchronized with the authoritative struct value `ul_config_req->ul_config_request_body.number_of_pdus`.

